(44, 9, 9, 32, 3, 6, 8, 'neither did eat nor drink', 'Fasting and Mourning Themes', 'Both passages emphasize a period of fasting and mourning. In Acts, Saul does not eat or drink for three days, while in Jonah, the king decrees that neither man nor beast should taste anything.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 9, 14, 33, 12, 13, 'three days without sight', 'Affliction and Humility in Prayer', 'This connection highlights the theme of affliction leading to humility and prayer. Both passages depict individuals in a state of distress, seeking God earnestly during their trials.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 9, 14, 33, 18, 19, 'three days without sight', 'Connection of Humility and Prayer', 'This connection highlights the theme of humility and seeking God. In Acts, the three days without sight may symbolize a period of reflection and repentance, similar to Manasseh''s prayer and humility in 2 Chronicles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 9, 17, 4, 16, 16, 'neither did eat nor drink', 'Fasting and Seeking Divine Favor', 'Both passages emphasize fasting without food or drink for three days. This connection highlights a period of intense spiritual preparation and seeking God''s intervention in critical situations.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 9, 44, 9, 11, 12, 'three days without sight', 'Saul''s Vision and Prayer', 'This connection highlights Saul''s state of prayer after three days of fasting and blindness. Both passages emphasize his spiritual transformation and preparation for healing.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 10, 1, 22, 1, 1, 'Behold, I am here, Lord', 'Divine Call and Response', 'Both passages emphasize a divine call followed by a responsive declaration of presence. Ananias and Abraham both respond with ''Behold, here I am,'' indicating readiness to serve.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 10, 44, 10, 3, 3, 'Behold, I am here, Lord', 'Divine Communication in Visions', 'Both passages emphasize divine communication through visions. Ananias and Cornelius each receive specific instructions from God, highlighting the theme of obedience to divine calls.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 10, 44, 22, 12, 12, 'Ananias', 'Connection of Ananias in Acts', 'Both passages emphasize Ananias as a significant figure in Damascus. The first passage introduces him as a disciple, while the second describes him as a devout man with a good reputation.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 10, 23, 6, 8, 8, NULL, 'Response to Divine Call', 'Both passages emphasize a readiness to respond to God''s call. Ananias says, ''Behold, I am here, Lord,'' similar to Isaiah''s ''Here am I; send me.'' This connection highlights the theme of willingness to serve God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 10, 1, 31, 11, 11, NULL, 'Divine Call Response', 'Both passages emphasize a personal response to God''s call, as Ananias and Jacob both reply, ''Here am I.'' This connection highlights the theme of divine communication and obedience.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 10, 2, 3, 4, 4, NULL, 'Divine Calling Response', 'Both passages emphasize a divine call to individuals, with Ananias and Moses responding, ''Here am I.'' This connection highlights the theme of obedience to God''s call.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 10, 9, 3, 4, 4, NULL, 'Divine Call Response', 'Both passages emphasize a divine call and the immediate response of the individual. Ananias and Samuel both reply with ''Here am I,'' indicating their readiness to serve.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 11, 44, 9, 30, 30, 'for, behold, he prayeth', 'Connection of Saul''s Journey', 'This connection highlights Saul''s transition from prayer to action. In Acts 9:11, Saul is identified as praying, and in Acts 9:30, he is sent forth to Tarsus, indicating a movement in his mission.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 11, 44, 21, 39, 39, 'called Saul, of Tarsus', 'Connection of Saul''s Identity', 'Both passages emphasize Saul''s identity as a man from Tarsus. The first passage introduces Saul as a significant figure in prayer, while the second passage reaffirms his Jewish heritage and citizenship in Tarsus.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 11, 42, 11, 9, 10, 'for, behold, he prayeth', 'Connection of Prayer and Seeking', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking and finding in both passages. In Acts, Saul is described as praying, while in Luke, the call to ask, seek, and knock emphasizes the importance of seeking divine assistance.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 11, 40, 7, 7, 8, 'for, behold, he prayeth', 'Connection of Prayer and Seeking', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking God through prayer. In Acts 9:11, Saul is described as praying, while Matthew 7:7 emphasizes that those who seek will find.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 11, 42, 18, 7, 14, 'for, behold, he prayeth', 'Prayer and Humility in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the act of prayer and the importance of humility before God. In Acts, Saul is described as praying, while in Luke, the publican''s humble prayer contrasts with the Pharisee''s self-righteousness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 11, 5, 4, 29, 29, 'for, behold, he prayeth', 'Seeking God in Prayer', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking God. In Acts, Saul is described as praying, while Deuteronomy emphasizes finding God when sought with all one''s heart and soul.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 11, 19, 50, 15, 15, 'for, behold, he prayeth', 'Prayer and Deliverance Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of prayer and divine response. In Acts, Saul is described as praying, while Psalms emphasizes calling upon God in times of trouble for deliverance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 12, 41, 5, 23, 23, NULL, 'Healing through the laying on hands', 'This connection highlights the act of laying hands as a means of healing. Both passages emphasize the importance of physical touch in the process of restoration and healing.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 9, 12, 44, 9, 10, 10, 'a man named Ananias coming in', 'Connection Between Ananias'' Vision', 'Both passages emphasize Ananias receiving a vision from the Lord. Acts 9:10 introduces Ananias, while Acts 9:12 describes his role in restoring sight. This connection highlights the divine guidance in Ananias'' mission.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
